  "slug": "cheese-and-onion-pasty",
  "title": "Cheese and Onion Pasty",
  "subtitle": "A shortcrust pastry half-moon filled with cheddar, potato, and raw onion",
  "excerpt": "The cheese and onion pasty is the vegetarian equivalent of the Cornish pasty. Raw potato, grated cheddar, and raw onion go into shortcrust pastry and bake together, producing a filling that is moist, savoury, and cohesive. Serve hot or cold.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Traditional British pasty. Cornish pasty tradition adapted for vegetarian filling. Jane Grigson, English Food (1974): pasty variations. Contemporary British bakery practice.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The cheese and onion pasty uses the same ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "raw filling",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr4ici00007cv4ixk8lv4z"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " method as the traditional Cornish pasty: the potato goes in raw and steams inside the sealed pastry. The cheddar melts into it during baking, and the raw onion sweetens and softens. The result needs the full 40-45 minutes at 200°C to cook the potato through.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Grate the potato on a coarse grater and pat dry: excess moisture is the main enemy. For the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "Cornish crimp",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpbcypms0000rsv4qq52nyjb"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " use your thumb and forefinger to fold and twist along the sealed top edge; for a simpler result, press with a fork.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you need",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
